articles.description: Isaiah Bailey turned in a career high 24 points, six boards, seven assists and four steals to help power Bethune-Cookman to an 87-67 win over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday.
articles.headline: Bethune-Cookman runs away from Maryland-Eastern Shore, 87-67

articles.description: Rob Marberry poured in 27 of his career-high 39 points in the second half and Lipscomb turned back North Florida 82-75 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Marberry scores 39 as Lipscomb tops North Florida 82-75

articles.description: Alante Fenner scored a career-high 46 points to lead Savannah State to a 97-94 overtime victory over Morgan State on Saturday.
articles.headline: Fenner scores 46, Savannah St. beats Morgan St. in OT, 97-94

articles.description: KJ Feagin had a career-high 32 points on 14-of-21 shooting and Santa Clara rallied from 11 down to beat San Diego 70-64 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Feagin with career-high 32, Santa Clara beats San Diego

articles.description: James Scott and Nick Masterson scored 20 points apiece and Kennesaw State beat Jacksonville 78-54 on Saturday, for its third straight win.
articles.headline: Scott, Masterson lead, Kennesaw St. beats Jacksonville 78-54

articles.description: Jamaal King scored 19 of his 25 points in the first half, Keith Braxton had 20 points and nine rebounds and St. Francis (Pa.) beat St. Francis (Brooklyn) 90-65 on Saturday.
articles.headline: St. Francis (Pa.) beats St. Francis (Brooklyn) 90-65
